<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="135" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[1986,2579,2702,3129]" pageId="6" pageNumber="135">
Classically treated as a member of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1832" box="[2083,2230,2820,2853]" class="Mammalia" family="Spalacidae" genus="Nyctocleptes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Nyctocleptes</taxonomicName>
, but R. Lopez-Antonanzas and colleagues in 2013 showed that extant species of 
<taxonomicName box="[2236,2353,2903,2932]" class="Mammalia" family="Spalacidae" genus="Rhizomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="135" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rhizomys</taxonomicName>
are very closely related with respect to known fossil taxa. Distributions of subspecies are poorly delineated, and multiple species may be present. Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
